<paragraph id="8BC236D5FF8EFFBF6EE2F96DFD16FE38" blockId="19.[151,1437,1728,2042]" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">
This is an intermediate-sized, pale-colored species, usually with a very bright yellow color pattern, especially when young (
<figureCitation id="13462A50FF8EFFBF6E98F949FEF1FFE4" box="[237,307,1764,1790]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="11.[151,250,730,754]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,706]" captionTargetId="figure-17@11.[151,1436,181,706]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 2. Photos of male Megalestes riccii showing color changes with maturing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4407487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4407487/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). The most conspicuous character of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D56FF8EFFBF6CA2F949FCFAFFE7" authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1934" box="[727,824,1764,1789]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="riccii">
<emphasis id="B909EAC7FF8EFFBF6CA2F949FCFAFFE7" box="[727,824,1764,1789]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">M. riccii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the yellow-colored cerci. This species is distributed in Guangxi, Hunan, Jiangxi, 
<collectingCountry id="F36A7645FF8EFFBF6FACF8A5FDECFE38" box="[473,558,1800,1826]" name="Taiwan" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, and Zhejiang.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C367655EFF8EFFB86EB2F881FD6BF8CB" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="265" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC236D5FF8EFFB86EB2F881FD6BF8CB" blockId="19.[151,1437,1728,2042]" lastBlockId="20.[151,1437,150,465]" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="265" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">
There were three named species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D56FF8EFFBF6C3BF881FD0EFE5C" authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1862" box="[590,716,1836,1862]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B909EAC7FF8EFFBF6C3BF881FD0EFE5C" box="[590,716,1836,1862]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">Megalestes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that have yellow-colored cerci, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D56FF8EFFBF6A44F881FB52FE5F" authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1934" box="[1073,1168,1836,1861]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="riccii">
<emphasis id="B909EAC7FF8EFFBF6A44F881FB52FE5F" box="[1073,1168,1836,1861]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">M. riccii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D56FF8EFFBF6AE8F881FB38FE5F" authorityName="Chen" authorityYear="1947" box="[1181,1274,1836,1861]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maai">
<emphasis id="B909EAC7FF8EFFBF6AE8F881FB38FE5F" box="[1181,1274,1836,1861]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">M. maai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D56FF8EFFBF6B43F881FA57FE5C" authorityName="Wilson &amp; Reels" authorityYear="2003" box="[1334,1429,1836,1862]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuska">
<emphasis id="B909EAC7FF8EFFBF6B43F881FA57FE5C" box="[1334,1429,1836,1862]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">M. tuska</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, all endemic to 
<collectingCountry id="F36A7645FF8EFFBF6F4AF8FDFE44FE70" box="[319,390,1872,1898]" name="China" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">China</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D56FF8EFFBF6FE4F8FDFD8DFE73" authorityName="Chen" authorityYear="1947" box="[401,591,1872,1898]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maai">
<emphasis id="B909EAC7FF8EFFBF6FE4F8FDFD8DFE73" box="[401,591,1872,1898]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">Megalestes maai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to 
<collectingCountry id="F36A7645FF8EFFBF6C8BF8FDFC96FE70" box="[766,852,1872,1898]" name="Taiwan" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
. We examined a series of type specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D56FF8EFFBF6B3BF8FDFF71FE97" authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1934" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="riccii">
<emphasis id="B909EAC7FF8EFFBF6B3BF8FDFF71FE97" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">M. riccii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
deposited in IZAS and IEAS, as well as photos of the 
<typeStatus id="54C68877FF8EFFBF6D51F8D9FC44FE94" box="[804,902,1908,1934]" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D56FF8EFFBF6DD8F8D9FBCCFE94" authorityName="Wilson &amp; Reels" authorityYear="2003" box="[941,1038,1908,1934]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuska">
<emphasis id="B909EAC7FF8EFFBF6DD8F8D9FBCCFE94" box="[941,1038,1908,1934]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">M. tuska</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, kindly provided by Dr. Guanhong Huang from the Agriculture, Fisheries and Conservation Department of 
<collectingCountry id="F36A7645FF8EFFBF6DBBF835FB95FEA8" box="[974,1111,1944,1970]" name="Hong Kong" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">Hong Kong</collectingCountry>
. After studying our series of specimens, including four specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D56FF8EFFBF6C11F811FD01FECF" authorityName="Chen" authorityYear="1947" box="[612,707,1980,2005]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maai">
<emphasis id="B909EAC7FF8EFFBF6C11F811FD01FECF" box="[612,707,1980,2005]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">M. maai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
kindly provided by Mr. Wen-chi Yeh and Dr. Liang-jong Wang from 
<collectingCountry id="F36A7645FF8EFFBF6EA0F84DFEE8FEE0" box="[213,298,2016,2042]" name="Taiwan" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, we found no distinct differences among these three. Molecular analysis also implied that they were the same species (
<figureCitation id="13462A50FF89FFB86F14FF3AFE67F9AB" box="[353,421,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1978,2002]" captionTargetBox="[213,1367,496,1949]" captionTargetId="figure-214@20.[211,1375,489,1954]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 7. Phylogenetic reconstruction from ITS data modified based on BI and ML trees, with both posterior probabilities (right) and bootstrap values (left) shown." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4407499" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4407499/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="265">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEC4B24FF89FFB86FCFFF3AFD84F9AB" author="Chao, H. - F." box="[442,582,150,177]" pageId="20" pageNumber="265" pagination="187 - 196" refId="ref13620" refString="Chao, H. - F. (1965) A study of the Chinese dragonflies of the genus Megalestes Selys, with description of a new species (Odonata: Synlestidae). Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 2, 187 - 196." type="journal article" year="1965">Chao (1965)</bibRefCitation>
compared a single male of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D56FF89FFB86D0EFF3AFC1AF9AA" authorityName="Chen" authorityYear="1947" box="[891,984,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maai">
<emphasis id="B909EAC7FF89FFB86D0EFF3AFC1AF9AA" box="[891,984,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="265">M. maai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F36A7645FF89FFB86A69FF3AFBACF9AB" box="[1052,1134,151,177]" name="Taiwan" pageId="20" pageNumber="265">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
with type specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D56FF89FFB86B0BFF3AFF10F9CE" authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1934" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="riccii">
<emphasis id="B909EAC7FF89FFB86B0BFF3AFF10F9CE" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="265">M. riccii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the results indicated that 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D56FF89FFB86C6EFF16FDBAF9CE" authorityName="Chen" authorityYear="1947" box="[539,632,187,212]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maai">
<emphasis id="B909EAC7FF89FFB86C6EFF16FDBAF9CE" box="[539,632,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="265">M. maai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was different from 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D56FF89FFB86D27FF16FC70F9CE" authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1934" box="[850,946,187,212]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="riccii">
<emphasis id="B909EAC7FF89FFB86D27FF16FC70F9CE" box="[850,946,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="265">M. riccii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the longer wings and the obtuse tip of the basal tooth on the paraproct. However, among our series of specimens, the body sizes of some Zhejiang individuals (
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D56FF89FFB86EB2FEAEFEEAF806" authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1934" box="[199,296,259,284]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="riccii">
<emphasis id="B909EAC7FF89FFB86EB2FEAEFEEAF806" box="[199,296,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="265">M. riccii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) were larger than those from 
<collectingCountry id="F36A7645FF89FFB86C0CFEAEFD09F807" box="[633,715,259,285]" name="Taiwan" pageId="20" pageNumber="265">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D56FF89FFB86CA9FEAEFCF8F806" authorityName="Chen" authorityYear="1947" box="[732,826,259,284]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maai">
<emphasis id="B909EAC7FF89FFB86CA9FEAEFCF8F806" box="[732,826,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="265">M. maai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and the shape of the paraproct basal tooth tip varied randomly. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEC4B24FF89FFB86F7BFE8AFDD1F85B" author="Wilson, K. D. P. &amp; Reels, G. T." box="[270,531,295,321]" pageId="20" pageNumber="265" pagination="237 - 279" refId="ref15245" refString="Wilson, K. D. P. &amp; Reels, G. T. (2003) Odonata of Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, China, Part 1: Zygoptera. Odonatologica, 32, 237 - 279." type="journal article" year="2003">Wilson &amp; Reels (2003)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D56FF89FFB86CBDFE8AFCEBF85B" authorityName="Wilson &amp; Reels" authorityYear="2003" box="[712,809,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuska">
<emphasis id="B909EAC7FF89FFB86CBDFE8AFCEBF85B" box="[712,809,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="265">M. tuska</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has “sharply pointed, bifurcated” tips of the basal tooth on the paraproct. Again, as discussed above, there is also intraspecies variation since our specimens show that both 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D56FF89FFB86EE2FEC2FF3AF893" authorityName="Wilson &amp; Reels" authorityYear="2003" box="[151,248,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuska">
<emphasis id="B909EAC7FF89FFB86EE2FEC2FF3AF893" box="[151,248,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="265">M. tuska</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D56FF89FFB86F44FEC2FE50F892" authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1934" box="[305,402,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="riccii">
<emphasis id="B909EAC7FF89FFB86F44FEC2FE50F892" box="[305,402,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="265">M. riccii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can have the tips obvious or not, and “bifurcated” or not. One individual from Jinxiu (very near the type locality of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D56FF89FFB86FD3FE3EFDC7F8B7" authorityName="Wilson &amp; Reels" authorityYear="2003" box="[422,517,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuska">
<emphasis id="B909EAC7FF89FFB86FD3FE3EFDC7F8B7" box="[422,517,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="265">M. tuska</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) even has a very long and pointed tip (
<figureCitation id="13462A50FF89FFB86DC3FE3EFBCBF8B7" box="[950,1033,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1443,1467]" captionTargetBox="[175,1424,244,1412]" captionTargetId="figure-56@15.[151,1437,237,1419]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 4. Caudal appendages of males (lateral view). a) australis; b) irma, paratype; c) distans, from Yaan, Sichuan; d) distans from Qingchengshan, Chengdu, Sichuan; e) heros; f) omeiensis, paratype; g) kurahashii; h) major; i) haui; j) “palaceus”; k) micans; l) “Chengi,” paratype; m) riccii; n) maai; o) tuska, from Damingshan, Guangxi; p) tuska, from Jinxiu, Guangxi. (Scale bar = 0.5 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4407493" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4407493/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="265">Fig. 4p</figureCitation>
). Thus, we believe that 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D56FF89FFB86B65FE3EFAAFF8B6" authorityName="Chen" authorityYear="1947" box="[1296,1389,403,428]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maai">
<emphasis id="B909EAC7FF89FFB86B65FE3EFAAFF8B6" box="[1296,1389,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="265">M. maai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D56FF89FFB86EE2FE1AFF3AF8CB" authorityName="Wilson &amp; Reels" authorityYear="2003" box="[151,248,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuska">
<emphasis id="B909EAC7FF89FFB86EE2FE1AFF3AF8CB" box="[151,248,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="265">M. tuska</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are both junior synonyms of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D56FF89FFB86C34FE1AFD60F8CA" authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1934" box="[577,674,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="riccii">
<emphasis id="B909EAC7FF89FFB86C34FE1AFD60F8CA" box="[577,674,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="265">M. riccii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
